CatDescriptText: Gladys Holt, secretary, Monessen, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column, published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 2, 1960, pg. A1 question reads: Do you think religion will play a major part in the choosing of the presidential candidate? If so, why?" Answer reads: "No. I think that the people will judge the candidates on their qualifications, and not religion."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Gladys Holt wearing dress with five buttons at waist and multi strand necklace and bracelet, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown; Portrait of woman wearing light colored dress with embroidered pattern along button placket, holding eyeglasses, seated on porch with woman in background
